HEADWORD: Serapis
<hw>Se*ra"pis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr.
<?/<?/<?/, <?/<?/<?/.]</ety> <fld>(Myth.)</fld> <def>An Egyptian deity,
at first a symbol of the Nile, and so of fertility; later, one of the
divinities of the lower world. His worship was introduced into Greece
and Rome.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

